COMP2322 Computer Networking Spring 2024

Well presented by Dr. Lou Wei. The lectures and labs of the subject go through the classical networking textbook Computer Networking: A Top-Down Approach. Hence, you may find plenty of materials to stabilize your learning from the internet, e.g., the official website of the textbook, the Wireshark lab notes of previous students, and tutorials given by other universities. The exams of the subject emphasize all the details that appears in the slides.

Learning Java/Python/Cpp socket programming libraries is strongly recommended for the project.